{
  "title": [
    "polymetro"
  ],
  "description": "polyrhythmic metronome",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "Triggers and Clocks"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "non-0 starts, zero stops"
        },
        {
          "type": "bang",
          "description": "syncs (restarts count) when polymetro is on"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "set tempo value in BPM"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "anything",
          "description": "multiplier as a float or fraction (anything/symbol)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "count for base rhythm"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "count for relative rhythm"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "tempo in BPM",
      "default": "120"
    },
    {
      "type": "symbol/float",
      "description": "polyrhythmic multiplier ratio",
      "default": "1/1"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [
    {
      "name": "-b",
      "description": "sets to bang mode output (instead of floats)"
    }
  ],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "tempo <float>",
      "description": "set tempo value in BPM"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[polymetro] is a polyrhythmic metronome. Polyrhythms are better specified with fractions, but you can set it as floats, which is a tempo multiplier value in the end. The left output is a counter for the base tempo count while the right outlet is the relative count/tempo as specified by the multiplier ratio. This is an abstraction based on synced [clock] objects."
}